# Decide the Gateway Redis Channel's Fate

## Question

Joel (2026-07-13, post-storm): "worth thinking if this needs to exist in our
world today with herdr observer running." The gateway redis channel was the
pre-herdr reflex arc: realtime signals (slack.signal.received, front
non-VIP notifies) queued in unTTL'd Redis lists to wake the interactive
ShitRat gateway persona. In today's world: memory is the observer's job
(30-min batch, durable pages), interaction is herdr sessions + the phone
line, and Redis-lists-as-pseudo-memory is exactly the unowned state the
storm grew in. Decide: (a) what genuinely needs REALTIME reflex (VIP email,
urgent pages) vs what is now observer/batch territory; (b) whether the
reflex arc's target should become "wake the right herdr session"
(herdr agent send) instead of a bespoke gateway loop; (c) retirement or
slimming path for the redis channel, with the storm-budget code kept
wherever pub/sub survives. Adjacent to the Observer/Bugle boundary grilling
— same redistricting, interaction lane.
